ted%20almost%20no%20excitement%2C%20and%20its%20reviews%20have%20been%20overwhelmingly%20negative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229e23e91c-4694-4f1e-8ca9-5fbd094f24be%5C%22%3EYouTube%20Recap%20is%20'AI%20garbage'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Reddit%2C%20users%20said%20YouTube's%20new%20Recap%20missed%20the%20mark.%20Many%20complained%20that%20it%20got%20their%20stats%20wrong%20and%20skipped%20the%20features%20they%20actually%20care%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYouTube%20is%20the%20main%20platform%20I%20watch%2C%20so%20I%20was%20excited%20to%20see%20they%20added%20a%20recap%20this%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20one%20user%2C%20who%20started%20a%20thread%20titled%20%26quot%3B2025%20YouTube%20recap%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-secret-to-avoiding-ai-slop-let-workers-job-craft-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20slop%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20their%20excitement%20quickly%20faded.%20The%20feature%20listed%20their%20top%20viewing%20interest%20as%20%26quot%3Bsewing%20tutorials%2C%26quot%3B%20even%20though%20the%20user%20said%20they%20had%20%26quot%3Bnever%20watched%20a%20sewing%20tutorial.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20clearly%20just%20AI%20garbage%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20user%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20agreed%20that%20most%20of%20the%20stats%20were%20%26quot%3Bflat-out%20wrong%2C%26quot%3B%20with%20several%20highlighting%20that%20the%20feature%20seemed%20to%20skew%20viewing%20interests%20toward%20AI-related%20topics%20they%20never%20engaged%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20Redditor%20wrote%20that%20YouTube%20didn't%20include%20two%20of%20the%20most%20fundamental%20metrics%3A%20total%20videos%20watched%20and%20total%20watch%20time.%20They%20called%20the%20Recap%20feature%20%26quot%3Blame%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20another%20user%20replied%2C%20%26quot%3BThat's%20all%20I%20really%20cared%20about.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20opened%20my%20YouTube%20Recap%20on%20my%20personal%20account%20and%20